<!-- ## Confidence Calibration Guide (reference for all spec files)
     9-10: Verified — tested, benchmarked, or explicitly confirmed by user
      7-8: Reviewed — design-reviewed or derived from authoritative docs
      5-6: Inferred — reasoned from code analysis or domain knowledge
      3-4: Hypothetical — educated guess, needs validation
      1-2: Speculative — placeholder, likely to change
     Source types: user (direct instruction), design-doc, code (analysis), inference, assumption
     When confidence ≤ 5 AND source = assumption, dossier status will flag a warning.

     ## Grounding Levels (reliability signal)
     Grounding indicates how well-evidenced a claim is, orthogonal to source:
       verified    — proven by code, tests, benchmarks, or direct observation
       reviewed    — design-reviewed, PR-approved, or user-confirmed (not yet code-proven)
       inferred    — reasoned from code analysis or domain knowledge (no direct proof)
       speculative — hypothesis, placeholder, or guess (needs validation)
     When grounding = speculative AND confidence > 5, dossier status will flag a warning.

     ## Source × Grounding common combinations
       source: user       + grounding: reviewed    (user stated, confirmed)
       source: code       + grounding: verified    (code-derived + tested)
       source: code       + grounding: inferred    (code patterns suggest)
       source: design-doc + grounding: reviewed    (doc reviewed)
       source: inference  + grounding: inferred    (reasoned from evidence)
       source: assumption + grounding: speculative (pure hypothesis)
     Uncommon: source: assumption + grounding: verified (contradictory — reconsider source)
