### FR-1: User Authentication
<!-- confidence: 8 | source: user -- >
**EARS Requirements:**
- WHEN the user submits the login form, the auth service SHALL validate credentials within 200ms.
- IF the JWT token is expired, THEN the auth middleware SHALL return HTTP 401 with a refresh token hint.
- WHILE the system is in maintenance mode, the API SHALL return HTTP 503 with a Retry-After header.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] AC-1.1: Given a registered user, When valid credentials are submitted, Then a JWT token is returned
- [ ] AC-1.2: Given an expired token, When sent in Authorization header, Then HTTP 401 is returned

